[{"category":"section","location":"predefined/#Predefined-types","page":"Predefined types","text":"Microfloats defines and exports a set of common types.","title":"Predefined types"},{"category":"section","location":"predefined/#IEEE-like","page":"Predefined types","text":"These types have IEEE 754-like Inf/NaN encodings, with Inf being represented as all 1s in the exponent and a significand of zero, and NaN being represented as all 1s in the exponent and a non-zero significand.","title":"IEEE-like"},{"category":"section","location":"predefined/#Finite","page":"Predefined types","text":"These types have no Inf encoding, with alternate or no NaN encodings at all.","title":"Finite"},{"category":"type","location":"predefined/#Microfloats.Float8_E5M2","page":"Predefined types","text":"Float8_E5M2\n\nProperties\n\nBits: 1 sign + 5 exponent + 2 significand (8 total)\nNon-finite behavior: Microfloats.IEEE\nHas Inf: true\nHas NaN: true\nMax normal: 57344.0\nMin positive: 6.103515625e-5\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.Float8_E5M2"},{"category":"type","location":"predefined/#Microfloats.Float8_E4M3","page":"Predefined types","text":"Float8_E4M3\n\nProperties\n\nBits: 1 sign + 4 exponent + 3 significand (8 total)\nNon-finite behavior: Microfloats.IEEE\nHas Inf: true\nHas NaN: true\nMax normal: 240.0\nMin positive: 0.015625\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.Float8_E4M3"},{"category":"type","location":"predefined/#Microfloats.Float8_E3M4","page":"Predefined types","text":"Float8_E3M4\n\nProperties\n\nBits: 1 sign + 3 exponent + 4 significand (8 total)\nNon-finite behavior: Microfloats.IEEE\nHas Inf: true\nHas NaN: true\nMax normal: 15.5\nMin positive: 0.25\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.Float8_E3M4"},{"category":"type","location":"predefined/#Microfloats.Float8_E4M3FN","page":"Predefined types","text":"Float8_E4M3FN\n\nProperties\n\nBits: 1 sign + 4 exponent + 3 significand (8 total)\nNon-finite behavior: Microfloats.NanOnlyAllOnes\nHas Inf: false\nHas NaN: true\nMax normal: 448.0\nMin positive: 0.015625\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.Float8_E4M3FN"},{"category":"type","location":"predefined/#Microfloats.Float8_E8M0FNU","page":"Predefined types","text":"Float8_E8M0FNU\n\nProperties\n\nBits: 0 sign + 8 exponent + 0 significand (8 total)\nNon-finite behavior: Microfloats.NanOnlyAllOnes\nHas Inf: false\nHas NaN: true\nMax normal: 1.7014118346046923e38\nMin positive: 5.877471754111438e-39\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.Float8_E8M0FNU"},{"category":"type","location":"predefined/#Microfloats.Float6_E3M2FN","page":"Predefined types","text":"Float6_E3M2FN\n\nProperties\n\nBits: 1 sign + 3 exponent + 2 significand (6 total)\nNon-finite behavior: Microfloats.FiniteOnly\nHas Inf: false\nHas NaN: false\nMax normal: 28.0\nMin positive: 0.25\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.Float6_E3M2FN"},{"category":"type","location":"predefined/#Microfloats.Float6_E2M3FN","page":"Predefined types","text":"Float6_E2M3FN\n\nProperties\n\nBits: 1 sign + 2 exponent + 3 significand (6 total)\nNon-finite behavior: Microfloats.FiniteOnly\nHas Inf: false\nHas NaN: false\nMax normal: 7.5\nMin positive: 1.0\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.Float6_E2M3FN"},{"category":"type","location":"predefined/#Microfloats.Float4_E2M1FN","page":"Predefined types","text":"Float4_E2M1FN\n\nProperties\n\nBits: 1 sign + 2 exponent + 1 significand (4 total)\nNon-finite behavior: Microfloats.FiniteOnly\nHas Inf: false\nHas NaN: false\nMax normal: 6.0\nMin positive: 1.0\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.Float4_E2M1FN"},{"category":"section","location":"microfloat/#The-Microfloat-type","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"","title":"The Microfloat type"},{"category":"section","location":"microfloat/#Defining-a-new-Microfloat","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"","title":"Defining a new Microfloat"},{"category":"section","location":"microfloat/#API","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"","title":"API"},{"category":"section","location":"microfloat/#Non-Finite-Behavior","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"","title":"Non-Finite Behavior"},{"category":"section","location":"microfloat/#Overflow-policies","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"","title":"Overflow policies"},{"category":"section","location":"microfloat/#Reflection","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"","title":"Reflection"},{"category":"type","location":"microfloat/#Microfloats.Microfloat","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"Microfloat <: AbstractFloat\n\nAbstract type for floating-point numbers that fit within a single byte.\n\nSee @microfloat for type declaration.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.Microfloat"},{"category":"macro","location":"microfloat/#Microfloats.@microfloat","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"@microfloat name [kwargs...]\n\nDefine a new type \n\nDefault policy rule: OVF when the type has any non-finite sentinel (IEEE or NanOnlyAllOnes), else SAT (forced for FiniteOnly since no sentinel encoding exists).\n\nKeyword arguments\n\nsign: Number of sign bits: 1 (default) or 0\nexponent: Number of exponent bits: ≥ 1\nsignificand: Number of significand / mantissa bits: ≥ 0\nnonfinite: IEEE (default), NanOnlyAllOnes, or FiniteOnly.\noverflow: Overflow handling during conversion from other types: SAT or OVF. Default: OVF if the type has any non-finite values (IEEE, NanOnlyAllOnes), otherwise SAT (FiniteOnly).\n\nExamples\n\nConverting from larger types rounds to the nearest even value, i.e. the value whose bit representation ends in 0.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.@microfloat"},{"category":"function","location":"microfloat/#Microfloats.hasinf","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"hasinf(::Type{<:Microfloat}) -> Bool\n\nReturn true if the type can represent Inf, otherwise false.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.hasinf"},{"category":"function","location":"microfloat/#Microfloats.hasnan","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"hasnan(::Type{<:Microfloat}) -> Bool\n\nReturn true if the type can represent NaN, otherwise false.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.hasnan"},{"category":"function","location":"microfloat/#Microfloats.non_finite_behavior","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"non_finite_behavior(::Type{<:Microfloat}) -> Type{<:NonFiniteBehavior}\n\nReturn IEEE, NanOnlyAllOnes, or FiniteOnly based on the assigned trait.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.non_finite_behavior"},{"category":"type","location":"microfloat/#Microfloats.IEEE","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"IEEE-754-style encoding of Inf and NaN.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.IEEE"},{"category":"type","location":"microfloat/#Microfloats.NanOnlyAllOnes","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"NaN encoded as all-ones in exponent+significand; no Inf.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.NanOnlyAllOnes"},{"category":"type","location":"microfloat/#Microfloats.FiniteOnly","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"No Inf or NaN — every bit pattern is a finite value.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.FiniteOnly"},{"category":"function","location":"microfloat/#Microfloats.overflow_policy","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"overflow_policy(T) -> Type{<:OverflowPolicy}\n\nRequired trait method on every concrete Microfloat subtype. Returns OVF or SAT. Registered by @microfloat.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.overflow_policy"},{"category":"type","location":"microfloat/#Microfloats.OVF","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"OVF\n\nOverflow conversion: out-of-range finite inputs go to ±Inf (IEEE) or NaN (NanOnlyAllOnes).\n\nInput Condition T has Inf+NaN T has NaN T is finite\nisnan(x) NaN NaN Error\nabs(x) > floatmax(T) ±Inf NaN Error\n\nExamples\n\njulia> @microfloat OverflowingFloat8 exponent=4 significand=3 overflow=Microfloats.OVF\n\njulia> OverflowingFloat8(10000)\nOverflowingFloat8(Inf)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.OVF"},{"category":"type","location":"microfloat/#Microfloats.SAT","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"SAT\n\nSaturating conversion: out-of-range finite inputs clamp to ±floatmax(T).\n\nInput Condition T has Inf+NaN T has NaN T is finite\nisnan(x) NaN NaN Error\nabs(x) > floatmax(T) ±floatmax ±floatmax ±floatmax\n\nExamples\n\njulia> @microfloat SaturatingFloat8 exponent=4 significand=3 overflow=Microfloats.SAT\n\njulia> SaturatingFloat8(10000)\nSaturatingFloat8(240.0)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.SAT"},{"category":"function","location":"microfloat/#Microfloats.bitwidth","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"bitwidth(::Type{<:AbstractFloat})\n\nReturns the number of utilized bits.\n\njulia> Microfloats.bitwidth(Float4_E2M1FN)\n4\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.bitwidth"},{"category":"function","location":"microfloat/#Microfloats.sign_bits","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"sign_bits(::Type{<:AbstractFloat})\n\nReturn the number of sign bits (between 0 or 1).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.sign_bits"},{"category":"function","location":"microfloat/#Microfloats.exponent_bits","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"exponent_bits(::Type{<:AbstractFloat})\n\nReturn the number of exponent bits.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.exponent_bits"},{"category":"function","location":"microfloat/#Microfloats.significand_bits","page":"The Microfloat type","text":"significand_bits(::Type{<:AbstractFloat})\n\nReturn the number of significand / mantissa bits.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Microfloats.significand_bits"},{"category":"section","location":"#Microfloats-Documentation","page":"Home","text":"","title":"Microfloats Documentation"},{"category":"section","location":"#Contents","page":"Home","text":"Pages = [\"index.md\", \"microfloat.md\", \"predefined.md\"]","title":"Contents"},{"category":"section","location":"#Index","page":"Home","text":"","title":"Index"}]
